    "The aim of measuring and analyzing eye movements is to study the user's attention, how he/she distributes it and what determines this distribution, which can be called attention tracking.",
    "Attention tracking in VR is a more comprehensive measure, aiming to gauge the depth of a user's cognitive engagement.",
    "It is not just about where users are looking, but how engrossed they are.",
    "By merging eye movement data with other metrics, such as the ones listed below, VR systems can deduce how captivating a particular scene or object is for the user (Duchowski 2017).",
